text.paragraph:
The primary efficacy endpoint was the change from baseline at week 12 (at least 4 hours after the last dose) in the 6 minute walk distance. Placebo-corrected mean increases in walk distance of 45 to 50 meters were observed with all doses of sildenafil. These increases were significantly different from placebo, but the sildenafil dose groups were not different from each other (see 
                        Figure 9
                     ), indicating no additional clinical benefit from doses higher than 20 mg three times a day. The improvement in walk distance was apparent after 4 weeks of treatment and was maintained at week 8 and week 12.
